title: New Holland Agriculture Publicly Launches the Industry's First All-Electric Utility Tractor with Autonomous Features ... - PR Newswire
summary: New Holland Agriculture has introduced the T4 Electric Power, the first all-electric utility tractor with autonomous features. This tractor is designed for lower horsepower field operations and is ideal for a variety of applications, including mixed farm, hay and forage, dairy, livestock, municipality, greenhouse, and specialty crops. The T4 Electric Power is equipped with a state-of-the-art lithium-ion battery pack and offers superior performance compared to diesel-powered tractors, including a 74 hp (55 kW) rated power and a 65 hp (48 kW) PTO power.
